<div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />ASM transition <strong>will</strong> be difficult to WLA-DX, I guarantee you.<br /><br />The most direct translation I found was .define:<br /><br />.define EquateVar1 1<br />.define EquateVar2 $02<br /><br />etc. Don't be mislead by the .define; it doesn't behave like the C preprocessor. The value it's defined to must be a numeric value, not just any text.<br /></div><br /><br />Thanks for the info on this, Blargg, If this doesn't work still, I'm going to really transfer to CA65 permanently<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=287">Hamtaro126</a> — Wed Aug 04, 2010 3:02 pm</p><hr />
