<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6744&amp;p=65421#p65421"><![CDATA[
ASM transition <strong>will</strong> be difficult to WLA-DX, I guarantee you.<br /><br />The most direct translation I found was .define:<br /><br />.define EquateVar1 1<br />.define EquateVar2 $02<br /><br />etc. Don't be mislead by the .define; it doesn't behave like the C preprocessor. The value it's defined to must be a numeric value, not just any text.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Wed Aug 04, 2010 1:07 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
